snippet.textDisplay: Here in the Philippines, we use sticks or tongs to get them and put them in a basket to shake off most of the spikes! We call the big one which can prick you right away Toyom and the other species Salawaki. Salawaki has less sharp barbs and can be handled without taking the spikes off and taste more creamy and sweet. Best eaten fresh with a couple drops of lime or lemon. The best way for first aid is you roast a lime or lemon in the coals then when they get warm. (caution not hot) sequence juice on the wound and the next day you will hardly feel a thing. I love all your videos dude! more power to you living the dream!
